Historic solar PV module prices (Swanson 2011)

Fig. 2 plots the (logarithm of) global average sales prices for solar PV modules against the (logarithm of) global cumulative installation capacity measured in megawatts. Average sales prices for PV modules have fallen from $81.62 W–1 in 1976 to $0.26 W–1 in 2019. In a minor variant of Swanson’s graph shown in Fig. 1, we estimate that the observed price declines are best described by a 79.2% constant elasticity learning curve for the time window 1976–2008. The corresponding R2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
